The paper proposes a novel algorithm for reinforcement learning that combines policy gradient methods and differentiable inductive logic programming. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The use of logic programming also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The experiments conducted on cliff-walking and blocks manipulation tasks suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Robotics (cs.RO) and Software Engineering (cs.SE).
